wikipedia_page.main: Elizabeth Carnegy-Arbuthnott (4 February 1906 – 24 January 1985) was a British fencer. She competed at the 1936 and 1948 Summer Olympics.She was president of the Soroptimist International of London Mayfair in 1969–70.
